            "answer_text": "Hello, A typical terabytes write figure for a 250 GB SSD lies b/w 60 and 150 tb written. That means, to get over a guaranteed TBW of 70, a user would have to write 190 GB daily over a period of year (In other words, to fill two thirds of the SSD with new data every day). ",
